channel.title: Winamp error
channel.description:
Whenever I queue two or more songs in Winamp, and sometimes when I replay a song, I get this error:
Winamp client version: 5.25 build 787 Beta Winamp caused an Access Violation (0xc0000005) in module ntdll.dll at 001b:7c91142e.
If anyone has an idea to what the fuck that means and/or how I could fix it, thanks. This just started recently with version 5.23, and I installed 5.25 because I thought it'd work.

sounds like a plugin error. I presume you have custome plug ins installed. Either remove / reinstall and it should sol;ve it, plug ins are no great loss when i comes to reinstalling and redownloading.
